Ls were generated (in particular, of the redirect URI) allowed for an attacker to steal secrets involved in setting up a user\u0026#39;s account (if the user hadn\u0026#39;t yet created an account, the hacker would be able to complete the account flow for them, then read all of their email), or would cause them to be redirected to an attacker controlled domain.\u003c/p\u003e\n"}]}